Wait, I realize this might cause bugs.

If top is initialized to 1000. If `delegatedQuery.skip` is 0 and people are querying logs after 1001, the following codes will just bypass these logs. Right? 

```
if (entryCount <= delegatedQuery.skip ||
                    entryCount > delegatedQuery.skip + delegatedQuery.top)
{
  continue;
}
```

Can we rearrange this a little now that we have a branch anyway to something like:

if (query.top && *query.top > arr->size()){
   arr->erase(arr->begin() + static_cast<ssize_t>(*query.top), arr->end());
}

The point of the old code was to avoid a branch entirely.
